One bright sunny morning I set of to work as a Nurse. I worked at [hospital]. About my daily chorees I Looked after patients and made sure that they were comfortable. I was working in the Childrens ward. I lived in [town] so I had to go a fair distance before I reached my destination. At work I gave* the children their breakefasts and then took* the finished plates to be washed. By the time I had a new patent in, gave the children their lunch and teas, and I got my own, I was quite egausted. Luckely I got home by nine o'clock where I had my supper and* went to bed.  Words: 113
